  <subsection xml:id="subsec-exploring-discuss">
    <title>Discuss</title>
    
    <paragraphs>
      <title>Discussion Board Forum</title>
      <p>
        Read or watch this guide on <q>Exploring data with graphs and summaries in R-Instat</q>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <ul>
          <li><p>The video can be viewed below: [Video: Exploring data with graphs and summaries]</p></li>
          <li><p>The guide can be found under <q>Tutorial 1</q>.</p></li>
          <li><p>Or, the guide can be downloaded from the resources.</p></li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <p>
        Apply to MICS (Kenya) and generate one graph and one summary table that tell you something about the data.
      </p>
      <p>
        <em>Post to the forum:</em>
        <ul>
          <li><p>Share your graph and summary (screenshots are fine).</p></li>
          <li><p>One insight you discovered (2<ndash/>4 sentences).</p></li>
          <li><p>One question this raises for further analysis.</p></li>
        </ul>
      </p>
      <p>
        <em>Reply to peers:</em> respond to at least two posts with either (a) a constructive question, or (b) a small suggestion that could improve their exploratory data analysis (e.g., <q>show % as well as counts</q>).
      </p>
    </paragraphs>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-exploring-assignment">
    <title>Assignment</title>
    
    <paragraphs>
      <title>Mini-Exploratory Data Analysis with Pivot Tables and Plots (MICS Kenya)</title>
      <p>
        <em>What to do:</em>
      </p>
      <p>
        Using any software of your choice produce:
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><em>Two pivot tables</em> that answer specific questions (e.g. How does a certain variable vary by region and urban/rural? Show counts and %).</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><em>Two plots</em> (e.g., histogram/boxplot for a numeric variable; bar chart for a categorical comparison).</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><em>Short interpretation</em> (max 500 words) explaining:
              <ul>
                <li><p>What the tables/plots show,</p></li>
                <li><p>Any anomalies or data issues spotted,</p></li>
                <li><p>Two follow-up questions you would investigate next and why.</p></li>
              </ul>
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </paragraphs>
    
    <paragraphs>
      <title>Deliverables</title>
      <p>
        <ul>
          <li><p>Upload a document with the four figures/tables embedded (clear titles/captions).</p></li>
          <li><p>Brief method notes: where the data came from, which variables used, any filters applied.</p></li>
        </ul>
      </p>
    </paragraphs>
  </subsection>

